{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"98d2fb24-e995-4883-b6c4-8a97929a8119","content":"There's no repo content here, so I'll answer from knowledge of Azure DevOps pipelines and MSTest.\n\n## Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nIn your `.csproj`, add:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis makes the test project a self-contained executable using Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform isn't compatible with `VSTest@3`. Use the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain `script` step) instead:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"\n```\n\n### 3. Publish TRX results\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Test Results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n```\n\n### 4. Publish code coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences from `VSTest@3`\n\n| Concern | Before (`VSTest@3`) | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | vstest.console | Built-in test host exe |\n| Task | `VSTest@3` | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` or `script: dotnet test` |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` argument |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled: true` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n\nThe `--logger trx` and `--collect` flags work the same whether you use `DotNetCoreCLI@2` or a raw `script: dotnet test` step.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"32fc738b-00c5-4dba-8d7b-8b696e893ca2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. I'll answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":667,"requestId":"1BDA:BB4CA:20F2A0C:2456D3C:6A03CED3"},"id":"8e772734-1f3d-4c03-8496-69d53ed67dd8","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:07:44.059Z","parentId":"fa2a9f12-3bc7-4128-95b1-41e9b189d840"}
